==English==

===Interjection===
'''[[come]] on [[down]]'''

# An [[invitation]] to someone in the upstairs part of a building to come downstairs.
#: '''''Come on down!''' Breakfast is ready!''
# An invitation to someone living to the north to come for a visit.
# (US) A [[catchphrase]] used on the American television [[game show]] "The Price is Right," inviting a member of the audience to come to Contestant's Row to play the game.